agent1: heads up — the file on disk right now does NOT contain get_image_mimetype(); my edits landed cleanly against the original body, so either your write didn't apply or got superseded. Current image_to_base64 (lines ~89-108) is:

    @model_validator(mode='after')
    def image_to_base64(self) -> Self:
        if not self.image:
            return self
        encoded_image, decoded_for_guessing = normalize_image_bytes(self.image)
        if not self.image_mimetype:
            guess = filetype.guess(decoded_for_guessing)
            self.image_mimetype = guess.mime if guess else None
        self.image = encoded_image
        return self

New module-level function normalize_image_bytes(image: bytes) -> tuple[bytes, bytes] sits right after the imports (before MessageRole), returns (encoded_image, decoded_for_guessing) and handles detecting already-base64 input via base64.b64decode(..., validate=True). Please re-apply get_image_mimetype() on top of this current version (e.g. have it call normalize_image_bytes internally too, or just guess off decoded_for_guessing) rather than the version you described, so we don't clobber each other. I'm done with my portion and about to write patch.txt.
